    "title": "Wiki Migration Guide",
    "description": "Moving from Rspress to Fumadocs",
    "content": "# Wiki Migration Guide\n\nThis document outlines the migration of the Vibe Trading Wiki from Rspress to a modern Next.js + Fumadocs stack.\n\n## Why migrate?\n\n- **Ecosystem Alignment:** Rspress was disconnected from the main project's Next.js/TypeScript architecture.\n- **Component Reuse:** Using Next.js allows sharing UI components and configurations between the main dashboard and the documentation.\n- **Enhanced DX:** Fumadocs provides a superior developer experience for MDX-based documentation with built-in search and better accessibility.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n### Framework\n- Replaced `rspress` with `next`, `fumadocs-ui`, and `fumadocs-core`.\n- Moved from Rspress routing to Next.js App Router.\n\n### Content Processing\n- Integrated `content-collections` for type-safe MDX processing.\n- Renamed `_meta.json` to `meta.json` to align with Fumadocs standards.\n\n### Styling\n- Adopted Tailwind CSS v4.\n- Synchronized color themes (OKLCH) and design tokens with the main `web` application.\n\n## How to add content\n\n1. Place MDX files in `apps/wiki/content/`.\n2. Define metadata in frontmatter.\n3. Configure sidebar hierarchy in `meta.json`.",
